<tr>
<td width=50%><font color=white>Posted By: Bladestorm sucks...</font></td><td width=50% align=right><font color=white>2000-03-09 09:48:10</font></td></tr><tr>
<td colspan=2 bgcolor="#0000AF"><font color=white>To answer all of the questions...<BR>
1) Bladestorm has the look of a katana. (IE, Electrum-Bladed Wakizashi)<BR>
2) Procs a 975 damage AE Rain spell. (Level 49 Magician nuke, "Rain of Swords")<BR>
Many believe you won't take max damage. This is, however, false. When you get hit, you get hit.<BR>
The only way to avoid this is by backstepping out of the line of fire.<BR>
3) Does not proc 5% of the time. It is based on dexterity.<BR>
I've gotten 6 procs in 35 swings. (Dexterity of 159). To assure you, a GM has stated that it is based on DEX, as well.<BR>
4) This weapon is an extremely rare drop off of Dracoliche.<BR>
I've run across two in my entire EQ life. I was lucky to recieve mine when we first dropped Thule. For all I know, he could still drop it...<BR>
But from what I've seen, it's been moved to Dracoliche.<BR>
5) I own this weapon. Along with many others. Personal favourite being Sunderfury.<BR>
I personally don't believe a warrior should wield a weapon bathed in a 'magical aura'. (This being opinion, of course).<BR>
It's a great weapon, don't get me wrong, and in all honesty, I use it on dragon/plane raids...<BR>
But other than that, you're much better off with a Monsoon, Sunderfury, or a Soul Leech. (Of course, this coming from a warrior with a 2H Slash fetish).<BR>
<BR>
<BR>
Adamant Swordswinger<BR>
Agnostic Human Warrior<BR>
49th Level - Damn Vox... She's going to pay.<BR>
"Why believe in a god... If the god in mention, would die before me?"</font></td></tr></table>
